    "b-component-themes-intro-2": {
      "id": "b-component-themes-intro-2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Each visual surface has its own token file inside a theme folder: "
        },
        {
          "insert": "components/<surface>.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ". Every color value is one string (both modes) or a "
        },
        {
          "insert": "{ light, dark }",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " pair. Non-color length and number tokens are always single strings. There is ONE FILE PER BLOCK-VOCABULARY TYPE (each type's own doc under 10-block-vocabulary states its keys) plus four non-block files. The vocabulary is CLOSED: files and keys must appear in "
        },
        {
          "insert": "THEME_TOKEN_REGISTRY",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "theme/theme-folders.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "), which maps each key to the tier-2 CSS variables it writes. Unknown files or keys are ignored, so a hand-edited theme can never break the app."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
